May’s private home sales up 17% month on month: URA:Source1. DEVELOPERS in Singapore sold 1 038 private homes in May  17 per cent higher than April’s take-up  but fewer than the 1 355 units they moved in the corresponding month a year earlier.2. This came as 1 595 private homes were launched in May – nearly double that of April’s 798 units  and nearly 30 per cent more than the 1 240 units released in May the year before.3. Of the private homes launched last month  the bulk were in the city fringe or Rest of Central Region  with 1 493 units released; the remaining 102 units were in the prime Core Central Region. None were launched in the suburbs or Outside Central Region.More here
